h_CronJob_To_v1beta1_CronJob\n- Convert_v1beta1_CronJobSpec_To_batch_CronJobSpec and Convert_batch_CronJobSpec_To_v1beta1_CronJobSpec\n- Convert_v1beta1_CronJobStatus_To_batch_CronJobStatus and Convert_batch_CronJobStatus_To_v1beta1_CronJobStatus\n- Identical TimeZone field conversion pattern as v1\n\n**Conversion Setup** (pkg/apis/batch/v1/conversion.go and v1beta1/conversion.go):\n- Field label conversion functions for selectable metadata fields\n- Both versions support querying by metadata.name, metadata.namespace, and status.successful\n\n## Defaulting Logic Differences\n\n**v1 Defaults** (pkg/apis/batch/v1/defaults.go):\n- SetDefaults_CronJob function defaults:\n  - ConcurrencyPolicy to AllowConcurrent if empty\n  - Suspend to false if nil\n  - SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit to 3 if nil\n  - FailedJobsHistoryLimit to 1 if nil\n- Uses modern ptr.To() utility functions for creating pointers\n\n**v1beta1 Defaults** (pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/defaults.go):\n- SetDefaults_CronJob function with identical defaults:\n  - ConcurrencyPolicy to AllowConcurrent\n  - Suspend, SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit (3), and FailedJobsHistoryLimit (1)\n- Uses legacy raw new() pointers and manual dereference pattern instead of ptr.To()\n\n**Auto-generated Defaults** (pkg/apis/batch/v1/zz_generated.defaults.go and v1beta1/zz_generated.defaults.go):\n- Additional auto-generated defaulting for JobTemplateSpec and other nested fields\n\n## Validation Logic\n\n**CronJob Validation** (pkg/apis/batch/validation/validation.go):\n- ValidateCronJobCreate: Creates validation including metadata name length check (must be <= 52 chars due to 11-char suffix added by controller)\n- ValidateCronJobUpdate: Updates validation with allowance for old CronJobs with longer names\n- validateCronJobSpec: Validates the spec with special handling for TimeZone changes\n  - Validates schedule format using cron/v3 parser\n  - Enforces constraint that both TZ in schedule AND timeZone field cannot be used simultaneously\n  - O